    <title>Touch User Guide</title>
    <para>
        <projectname>Touch</projectname> is the application that comes with the textbook 
        <emphasis>A Touch of Class</emphasis>. It is the framework for the examples and exercises
        that you find in the book. <emphasis>A Touch of Class</emphasis> is used to teach programming to
        students in the first semester. The examples are based on <libraryname>TRAFFIC</libraryname>
        [<link url="references.html">sa05</link>] a library that models a city and its
        transportation connections. The visual presentation is done using <libraryname>EiffelMedia</libraryname> 
        (which is further development of <libraryname>ESDL</libraryname> [<link url="references.html">tgb03</link>])
    </para>
    <para> This document describes how to use <projectname>Touch</projectname> and is structured
